content:
Set Up Your Development Environment for Machine Learning Models

Your development environment must include Python 3.7 and either TensorFlow 2.7.0 or Scikit-learn 1.0.2.

TensorFlow:

* Software: Python 3.7, TensorFlow 2.7.0
* Description: End-to-end open source platform for machine learning.
* Download from: https://pypi.org/project/tensorflow/2.7.0

Supported components:
absl-py v0.13.0
google-auth v1.28.0
protobuf v3.14.0
tensorflow-probability v0.12.1
tensorflow-recommenders v0.6.0

Pandas: 1.0.5, NumPy: 1.19.5
Other Libraries and Modules:
bandit v1.6.2
gitdb v4.0.5
PyYAML v5.4.1
marshmallow v3.3.0
scikit-learn v0.24.2
joblib v1.0.0
scipy v1.7.1
threadpoolctl v2.2.0

Scikit-Learn:

* Software: Python 3.7, Scikit-learn 1.0.2
* Description: Machine learning in Python. Simple and efficient tools for predictive data analysis.
* Download from: https://pypi.org/project/scikit-learn/1.0.2/#files

Supported components:
bandit v1.6.2
gitdb v4.0.5
gitpython v3.1.24
pbr v5.7.0
importlib-metadata v4.8.2
marshmallow v3.3.0
PyYAML v5.4.1
six v1.15.0
typing-extensions v3.7.4.3
zipp v3.6.0
title: Setting Up Development Environment for Machine Learning
